      "markdown": "# üíõ B6 ‚Äî Gustar-type Verbs (B1)\n\n**Goal:** Learn how to use verbs like **gustar** that describe what **pleases you** (not what you do). They use **indirect object pronouns** and **3rd person verb forms.**\n\n---\n\n## ‚öôÔ∏è Structure\n- **me / te / le / nos / os / les** + **gusta / gustan**\n- Verb agrees with the **thing liked**, not the person\n\n**Ejemplos:**\n- *Me gusta el caf√©.* ‚Üí I like coffee  \n- *Nos gustan los libros.* ‚Üí We like books\n\n> üí° Word order can change: *El caf√© me gusta mucho.*\n\n---\n\n## üìå IO Pronouns Table\n| Person         | Pronoun |\n|----------------|----------|\n| yo             | me       |\n| t√∫             | te       |\n| √©l/ella/usted  | le       |\n| nosotros/as    | nos      |\n| vosotros/as    | os       |\n| ellos/ellas/ustedes | les  |\n\n---\n\n## üí° Common Gustar-type Verbs\n- **encantar** (to love) ‚Äî *Me encanta la m√∫sica.*\n- **interesar** (to interest) ‚Äî *Les interesa el arte.*\n- **molestar** (to bother) ‚Äî *¬øTe molesta el ruido?*\n- **doler** (to hurt) ‚Äî *Me duele la cabeza.*\n\n---\n\n> üìù Always use 3rd person verb forms and match number (gusta/gustan).\n",
